Project: ReGen PEPT
Module: Restricted Knowledge Section (Enhanced FAQ)
Priority: Critical
Platform: Desktop First

Objective:
Fix incorrect access blocking for registered users and build the enhanced FAQ structure organized by Protocol and Product. The section must be accessible only to verified users, but must correctly recognize authenticated users and render the FAQ content once available.

Part 1 — Fix Access Control Logic

Problem:
The system displays "Restricted Access" even when the user is logged in. The header confirms authenticated session, but authorization logic fails.

Required Behavior:

A user should be allowed to access this section if:

user.isAuthenticated == true
AND
(
user.role == "verified_medical"
OR
user.role == "clinic"
OR
user.role == "pharmacy"
OR
user.role == "distributor"
OR
user.isVerified == true
)

Only block users when:

user.isAuthenticated == false

OR

user.role == "guest"
AND
user.isVerified != true

Implementation Rules:

1. Do not rely only on frontend state.
2. Validate role using session token payload.
3. Confirm hydration after login.
4. Reload role state after authentication.

Add debugging logs:

log.user.role
log.user.isVerified
log.sessionLoaded

If access denied:

Show diagnostic message in console:

ACCESS_DENIED_REASON:
- missing_role
- not_verified
- session_not_loaded

UI Rule:

If user is authenticated but not verified:

Show:

"Your account is registered but not yet verified.
Please contact support to activate professional access."

Instead of generic Restricted Access.

